import sqlite3
import pandas

#-------------------------
#--------Part 1-----------
#-------------------------
sqlite_file = 'lahman2014.sqlite'
conn = sqlite3.connect(sqlite_file)
cursor = conn.cursor()

cursor.execute("CREATE TABLE new_salaries AS SELECT yearID, teamID, SUM(salary) AS budget FROM Salaries WHERE lgID == 'AL' GROUP BY teamID, yearID")
cursor.execute("CREATE TABLE new_teams AS SELECT yearID, teamID, franchID, G, W, L, name FROM Teams")
cursor.execute("ALTER TABLE new_teams ADD winpercent as (cast(W as float)/cast(G as float)*100) ")
team_data = pandas.read_sql("SELECT * FROM new_teams t INNER JOIN new_salaries s ON (t.teamID = s.teamID AND t.yearID = s.yearID)", conn)

team_data

#I used inner join for this merge between teamIDs so any teams with missing rows on either table will have been removed.

#Problem 4
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

from matplotlib.lines import Line2D # for the legend
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

team_data['bins'] = pandas.cut(team_data["yearID"],[1990,1995,2000,2005,2010,2014],include_lowest=True)
grouped_data = team_data.groupby(['bins','teamID']).mean().reset_index().dropna()



#PLOT 1
budgetdata = grouped_data[grouped_data['bins'] == pandas.Interval(left=1989.999,right=1995.0)]['budget']
winpercent = grouped_data[grouped_data['bins'] == pandas.Interval(left=1989.999,right=1995.0)]['winpercent']
teamID = grouped_data[grouped_data['bins'] == pandas.Interval(left=1989.999,right=1995.0)]['teamID']

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8));
ax.scatter(budgetdata,winpercent)

linear_regressor = LinearRegression()
linear_regressor.fit(budgetdata.values.reshape(-1,1), winpercent)
x_pred = np.linspace(budgetdata.min(), budgetdata.max(), num=200).reshape(-1, 1)
y_pred = linear_regressor.predict(x_pred)  
ax.plot(x_pred, y_pred, color="#696969", lw=4)
for index in range(budgetdata.size):
  ax.text(budgetdata.iloc[index], winpercent.iloc[index], teamID.iloc[index], size=12)

#Problem 5
mean = team_data.groupby(["yearID"])["budget"].mean()
stddev = team_data.groupby(["yearID"])["budget"].std()

def standardize(row):
    return (row['budget']-mean[row['yearID']])/stddev[row['yearID']]

team_data["std_payroll"] = team_data.apply(lambda row: standardize(row), axis=1)

#Problem 6
team_data['bins'] = pandas.cut(team_data["yearID"],[1990,1995,2000,2005,2010,2014],include_lowest=True)
grouped_data = team_data.groupby(['bins','teamID']).mean().reset_index().dropna()


#PLOT 1
budgetdata = grouped_data[grouped_data['bins'] == pandas.Interval(left=1989.999,right=1995.0)]['std_payroll']
winpercent = grouped_data[grouped_data['bins'] == pandas.Interval(left=1989.999,right=1995.0)]['winpercent']
teamID = grouped_data[grouped_data['bins'] == pandas.Interval(left=1989.999,right=1995.0)]['teamID']

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8));

linear_regressor = LinearRegression()
linear_regressor.fit(budgetdata.values.reshape(-1,1), winpercent)
x_pred = np.linspace(budgetdata.min(), budgetdata.max(), num=200).reshape(-1, 1)
y_pred = linear_regressor.predict(x_pred)  
ax.plot(x_pred, y_pred, color="#696969", lw=4)
for index in range(budgetdata.size):
  ax.text(budgetdata.iloc[index], winpercent.iloc[index], teamID.iloc[index], size=12)

#Problem 8
team_data['expected_winpct'] = team_data['std_payroll']*2.5+50
team_data['efficiency'] = team_data['winpercent'] - team_data['expected_winpct']

teams_to_plot = ['OAK', 'BOS', 'NYA', 'ATL', 'TBA']
plot_df = team_data[team_data['teamID'].isin(teams_to_plot)]

#Plot code from above
budgetdata = plot_df['yearID']
winpercent = plot_df['efficiency']
teamID = plot_df['teamID']

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8));
ax.scatter(budgetdata,winpercent)

linear_regressor = LinearRegression()
linear_regressor.fit(budgetdata.values.reshape(-1,1), winpercent)
x_pred = np.linspace(budgetdata.min(), budgetdata.max(), num=200).reshape(-1, 1)
y_pred = linear_regressor.predict(x_pred)  
ax.plot(x_pred, y_pred, color="#696969", lw=4)
for index in range(budgetdata.size):
  ax.text(budgetdata.iloc[index], winpercent.iloc[index], teamID.iloc[index], size=12)
